---
// A static recreation of the hybrid-retrieval diagram from euterria.org's
// "under the hood" page: one question fans out to keyword + semantic
// search, the candidates blend, and a reranker decides the final order.
---
<figure class="eutf">
  <div class="eutf-card">
    <div class="eutf-row eutf-row--query">
      <span class="eutf-stage-label">Question</span>
      <div class="eutf-pill">&ldquo;Who&rsquo;s working on urban heat in Oakland?&rdquo;</div>
    </div>

    <div class="eutf-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="eutf-row eutf-row--split">
      <div class="eutf-branch">
        <span class="eutf-stage-label">Keyword search</span>
        <div class="eutf-chip">Oakland Shade Plan</div>
        <div class="eutf-chip">Heat &amp; Health Report</div>
      </div>
      <div class="eutf-branch">
        <span class="eutf-stage-label">Semantic search</span>
        <div class="eutf-chip eutf-chip--sem">Dr. Maya Okonkwo</div>
        <div class="eutf-chip eutf-chip--sem">&ldquo;…tree-canopy gaps in flatland heat&rdquo;</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="eutf-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="eutf-row eutf-row--query">
      <span class="eutf-stage-label">Reranked by meaning</span>
      <div class="eutf-pill eutf-pill--result">Dr. Maya Okonkwo → Oakland Shade Plan → GreenLine Collaborative</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <figcaption>How a question becomes a ranked answer: keyword and semantic retrieval run in parallel, then a reranker sorts the blended results by what the question actually means.</figcaption>
</figure>
